Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Literacy Outreach Coordinator Prince George , BC Description Position Title: Literacy Outreach Coordinator (LOC) Reports to: Prince George Literacy Advisory Committee (PGLAC)Role Overview: The Literacy Outreach Coordinator (LOC) works in partnership with the Prince George Literacy Advisory Committee (PGLAC) to implement the objectives of the Literacy Prince George Strategic Plan. This role is a part-time contract position, functioning as an independent contractor.Key Responsibilities:The LOC will coordinate community-based literacy programs and initiatives with a focus on raising awareness and promoting literacy across diverse areas, including family literacy, adult literacy, and financial literacy, among others. Responsibilities include:Program Development and Coordination: Research training resources and support the selection of suitable literacy training models.Recruit agencies and organizations to engage in literacy initiatives.Organize workshops and learning opportunities based on community needs.Promote programs and reach out to potential learners in the community.Perform additional duties as needed to advance literacy goalsCommunity Engagement and Awareness: Advocate for literacy initiatives, covering areas such as digital literacy, health literacy, civic literacy, numeracy, and workplace literacy.Deliver presentations to local groups (e.g., Rotary, Kiwanis) and participate in community literacy boards.Prepare and submit annual reports to Decoda Literacy Solutions, funders, PGLAC, and relevant provincial government entities.Reporting and Compliance:Prepare and submit annual reports to Decoda Literacy Solutions, funders, PGLAC, and relevant provincial government entities.Fundraising Coordination:Oversee the Raise a Reader fundraiser, including:Recruiting and managing volunteers.Securing financial sponsorship from local organizations.Coordinating collection points and donation efforts.Managing grant applications and the distribution process.Collaboration and Networking:Engage with literacy organizations and programs, both locally and regionally.Represent PGLAC at community, regional, and provincial meetings.Maintain communication records and update the PGLAC on ongoing efforts.Support for Literacy PractitionersFacilitate the development of literacy programs and resources.Coordinate the administration of funds for community literacy events.Foster partnerships among literacy workers and help disseminate best practices.Professional Deveopment Stay informed of current literacy trends through research and participation in professional development opportunities.Other Duties Complete miscellaneous tasks that support literacy efforts in the community as assigned.Required Qualifications:Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience.Proven experience in organizing events, program coordination, and community outreach.Strong network of community contacts.Excellent communication, interpersonal, research, and presentation skills.Proficiency with digital tools and technologies.Evidence of ongoing professional development.Ability to write reports and meet deadlines.Literacy practitioner experience and fundraising experience are assets.Desired Personal Attributes: Self-motivated with the ability to work independently.Strong team-building and collaboration skills.Adaptability in a dynamic work environment.Creative problem-solving abilities.Strong organizational and time-management skills.Knowledge of various topics, including current trends, events, and media.Terms of Employment Position Type: Part-time, contract-based (home office).Hours: 37.5 to 75 hours per month (with potential for additional hours based on available grant funding).Compensation: $28.00 per hour.Start Date: January 6th, 2025.Email Resume and Cover Letter to: locprincegeorge@gmail.com Compensation $28.00 Closes: 22 November, 2024 Prince George Literacy Advisory Commitee Prince George , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
