 support of education, networking, collaboration, and inspiration Qualifications Completion or impending completion of a Master of Library and Information Studies from an ALA Accredited University. (Fall 2024 grads are welcome to apply) Exceptional customer service and communication skills Strong interpersonal skills and ability to work effectively with a variety of groups Strong Technology Skills The successful candidate must be in possession of a Class 5 GDL, Class 5 Alberta licence, or other Canadian province/territory equivalent driver’s license. Access to a reliable vehicle is also an asset. Benefits Salary range $66,498.36 - $81,746.26 Opportunity to work remotely Opportunity to explore communities across Northeastern Alberta Competitive benefits package Employee Family Assistance Program (EFAP) How to Apply If MLS Consultant sounds like the next chapter in your career, take this opportunity to make a real contribution to one of Alberta’s largest growing public library systems. Please send a cover letter and resume to jmorris@nlls.ab.ca. Be sure to quote competition number “#2024-002 MLS Consultant” in the subject line of your e-mail. Interviews for this competition will commence after November 1, 2024. However, the competition will remain open until a successful candidate is found. We thank all who apply but only those selected for an interview will be contacted. NLLS values diversity and inclusion and welcomes diverse expertise and talent to support an innovative and collaborative work environment. We are committed to a respectful and inclusive workplace and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Any personal information submitted will be managed in accordance with the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act and will be used only to determine eligibility for employment. Canadian citizens and permanent residents of Canada will be given priority. Applicants must be legally eligible to work in Canada. Compensation $66,498.36 - $81,746.26 Closes: 9 January, 2025 Northern Lights Library System Elk Point , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
